- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of coordinated multipoint (CoMP) communications in small-cell networks to improve data rates and cell-edge throughput. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper derives the achievable rates of the SBS cooperation strategies. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper discusses the network energy efficiency of the fractal small-cell networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper discusses the improvement of data rates in small-cell networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely possibility as there is no mention of security or cryptography in the paper.
